title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 7
text:
Sept 29 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:
Top economic events
Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily *** TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 29 TOKYO - OECD E-Leaders 2015 (to Sept. 30). OECD Deputy Secretary General Mari Kiviniemi will deliver opening remarks. MUMBAI, India - Reserve Bank of India holds monetary policy meeting, to announce interest rates. MAKATI CITY - Central bank of Philippines Governor Amando Tetangco speaks at joint general assembly of local fixed income, currency and trust market associations - 1030 GMT. NAIROBI - Central bank of Kenya Governor Patrick Njoroge holds a press conference - 0730 GMT. WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 30 WASHINGTON - International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde participates in conversation hosted by the Council of Americas on global economic policies and prospects - 1430 GMT. BUCHAREST - Central bank of Romania holds board meeting, to announce interest rates - 0700 GMT. BANGKOK - Central bank of Thailand releases its economic forecast - 0030 GMT. BANGKOK - Central bank of Thailand will publish the minutes of September policy meeting - 0200 GMT. THURSDAY, OCTOBER 1 PRAGUE - European Central Bank banking supervision chief Daniele Nouy speaks at the ESE Conference 2015 "Financial supervision in Europe - on the right track?" organized by Deutsche Bundesbank in Prague - 1110 GMT. FRIDAY, OCTOBER 2 PRAGUE - Czech National Bank will publish the minutes of September governing board meeting - 0700 GMT. MONDAY, OCTOBER 5 MEXICO CITY - Central Bank of Mexico publishes the minutes of September monetary policy meeting - 1400 GMT. WARSAW - National Bank of Poland holds Monetary Policy Council meeting (to Oct. 6) TUESDAY, OCTOBER 6 LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on the World Economic Outlook - 1400 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Ensuring Inclusive Development: Good Practices in Promoting Accountability in Latin America" - 1700 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Labor Market's Impact from the Slowdown in Latin America" - 1900 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank holds Youth Dialogue - 2030 GMT. LIMA - World Bank holds a discussion on Social Inclusion: WikiStage and World Bank Group Lima Special Event - 2200 GMT. Speakers:- World Bank President Jim Yong Kim and World Bank Managing Director Sri Mulyani Indrawati. BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary non-rate-setting meeting. WARSAW - National Bank of Poland announces rate decision - 0930 GMT. WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 7 BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary will publish the minutes of September policy meeting - 1200 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on Global Financial Stability Report - 1400 GMT. LIMA - The IMF holds a discussion on "Capacity Development in Latin America and the Caribbean and the Way Forward" - 1430 GMT. Speakers:- IMF Deputy Managing Director Carla Grasso and Central Bank of Jamaica Governor Brian Wynter. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Flagship: Inequality, Opportunity and Prosperity" - 1500 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on Fiscal Monitor - 1530 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on Ideas for Action: Youth Engagement for Financing the Future of Development - 1600 GMT. LIMA - IMF holds a discussion on "Bridging the Pacific: Harnessing The Benefits Of Rising Trade And Financial Integration Between Asia". Speakers:- IMF First Deputy Managing Director David Lipton and People Bank of China Deputy Governor Yi Gang. LIMA - World Bank holds a discussion on "Building on Peru's Success: Boosting Productivity for Faster Growth". Speakers: World Bank President Jin Yong Kim, Peru Finance Minister Alonso Segura and Polish Finance Minister Mateusz Szczurek. LIMA - IMF holds a Conversation on Climate Change. Speakers: International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde and World Bank President Jin Yong Kim. LIMA - IMF holds a discussion "Energy Pricing-Getting it Right". Speakers: International Monetary Fund Deputy Managing Director Min Zhu and Former Irish President Mary Robinson.
